From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Armbian <root@armbian>
Date: Thu, 19 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: board-nanopi-r4s: add PCIe bus scan delay

The 2nd Ethernet port on NanoPi R4S uses a Realtek RTL8111/RTL8125
connected via PCIe. Without a delay, the PCIe bus scan may happen before
the PHY is fully initialized, causing intermittent timeout errors.

This is similar to RockPro64 which also needs a 1000ms delay.
See: rk3399-rp64-pcie-Reimplement-rockchip-PCIe-bus-scan-delay.patch

---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-nanopi-r4s.dtsi | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-nanopi-r4s.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-nanopi-r4s.dtsi
index 8d94d9f91a5c..851e81d29195 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-nanopi-r4s.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/rockchip/rk3399-nanopi-r4s.dtsi
@@ -74,6 +74,7 @@ &pcie0 {
 	max-link-speed = <1>;
 	num-lanes = <1>;
 	vpcie3v3-supply = <&vcc3v3_sys>;
+	bus-scan-delay-ms = <1000>;
 };

 &pinctrl {
--
Armbian
